 Optical Interconnects for the Design of Large Scale Symmetric Multiprocessors   Project Motivation 
Symmetric multiprocessors (SMPs) are attractive parallel computers widely used, since they provide a global physical address space and a symmetric access to the entire memory with increased flexibility and programmability. SMPs use fast snooping protocols to maintain cache coherence by broadcasting every request on the shared bus connecting all modules.

